<h1>Case 5 — Central Security & Smart Surveillance Control Room</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Central Security & Smart Surveillance Control Room manages Velora’s entire safety ecosystem, 
including CCTV cameras, motion sensors, emergency alerts, and real-time response coordination. 
It automates threat identification and supports quick decision-making for citywide safety.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Manual monitoring leads to missed threats and delayed alerts.</li>
    <li>High number of false alarms slows down security operations.</li>
    <li>Difficulty in locating the nearest available security personnel.</li>
    <li>Poor coordination across different surveillance zones.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Maintain camera and sensor records for instant identification.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> Sort alerts based on severity and urgency.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Manage multiple incoming alerts efficiently.</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Find the closest security officer or patrol route.</li>
    <li><strong>BFS:</strong> Scan nearby camera feeds for threat expansion.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 16 — Peace, Justice & Strong Institutions</strong>
    <p>Supports reliable and secure public safety systems for citizens.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Creates safer urban zones through smart surveillance and monitoring.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Uses modern algorithms and digital tools for city-level security innovation.</p>
</div>

